X) XWAIT

SYNTAX:

   XWAIT HH:MM[:SS] [[MM-DD-YY] TOMORROW,SUN,MON,TUE,WED,THU,FRI,SAT]

 Waits until a specified time, or a key is pressed. If ^C is pressed a code
 of 20 is returned, if ^D ^E or ^F is pressed a code of 10 is returned, if
 the time arrives to stop waiting then a 0 is returned. If an error occurs
 30 is returned.

 The command line arguments are given as a time and a date. XWAIT will stop
 waiting when the time is greater than or equal to that given.


